                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2434</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-13T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1916, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Official statement reported given out in Japan to the effect that foreigners in
                    China desire more protection has no foundation. Conditions <pb facs="0161"
                        n="85" xml:id="pg_85"/> here are again perfectly normal, with no
                    apprehension on the part of foreigners and with a feeling of confidence in
                    assured realization of economic political progress under the Republic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
